      "markdown": "# üì¢ B12 ‚Äî Imperatives + Pronoun Placement (B1)\n\n**Goal:** Give commands and instructions with correct pronoun use.**\n\n---\n\n## üìå Affirmative Imperatives\n\n| Person | -AR | -ER/-IR |\n|---|---|---|\n| t√∫ | **-a** | **-e** |\n| vosotros | **-ad** | **-ed/-id** |\n| usted | **-e** | **-a** |\n| ustedes | **-en** | **-an** |\n\n**Examples**\n- *Habla (t√∫)* ‚Äî Speak  \n- *Comed (vosotros)* ‚Äî Eat  \n- *Escriba (usted)* ‚Äî Write\n\n**Irregular t√∫ affirmatives**  
ven (venir), di (decir), sal (salir), haz (hacer), ten (tener), ve (ir), pon (poner), s√© (ser)\n\n---\n\n## üìå Negative Imperatives\n\nUse **present subjunctive forms**\n- *No hables (t√∫), no habl√©is (vosotros), no hable (usted)*\n- *No comas, no com√°is, no coma‚Ä¶*\n\n---\n\n## ‚ö° Pronoun Placement\n- **Affirmative** ‚Üí after & attached: *d√≠melo*, *lev√°ntate*\n- **Negative** ‚Üí before: *no me lo digas*, *no te levantes*\n\n**Accent**: add written accent if adding 2 pronouns (e.g. *d√≠melo*, *c√≥metelo*)\n\n---\n\n> üìù Summary:  
> Affirmative: verb + pronoun(s) (attach)  
> Negative: no + pronoun(s) + verb (before)\n",
